article.headline: Austin Peay 75, Tennessee State 71
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Josh Lewis and Anthony Davis both scored 17 points Tuesday night as Austin Peay held off Tennessee State 75-71 in the first round of the Ohio Valley Conference tournament. The Governors (20-8) won their 28th consecutive game at home and advanced to the semifinals, where they will face Eastern Kentucky on Friday. Roshaun Bowens led the Tigers (7-21) with 18 points while Bruce Price, Garrett Richardson and Jeremy Jackson had 13 points each. Tennessee State finished with five more wins than last season in coach Cy Alexander's first year with the program. The teams traded the lead five times in the first half, with neither team able to take a lead of more than five points. Austin Peay led 14-9 with 14:39 left on a layup by Lewis. Tennessee State took a 26-21 lead at the 8:55 mark on a 3-pointer by Jackson, who hit three 3s on the night. The Tigers took a 39-38 lead at halftime. A jump shot by Davis gave Austin Peay a 60-52 with 10:19 to play, but Tennessee State fought back and got within 68-67 with 4:51 left on a 3-point shot by Richardson. That was as close as the Tigers would get. A Davis 3-pointer with 2:08 to play gave the Governors a 74-69 lead, and they held on for the win. Rhet Wierzba scored 11 points for Austin Peay and Davis had 12 rebounds. Austin Peay was 21-of-30 from the free throw line, while Tennessee State was 7-of-8. The victory was the 300th in the career of Austin Peay coach Dave Loos. He won 82 games at Christian Brothers in Memphis before taking over at Austin Peay in 1990.
